<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                            <head><persName type="from">Mr. Dix</persName> to <persName type="to">M.
                                    Moustier</persName></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                            States</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Paris,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-14"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 14, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to inform you that
                                Mr. Samuel B. Ruggles is authorized by my government to attend the
                                international conference in regard to the uniformity of coinage, to
                                be held at Paris on the 17th instant. The despatch giving me this
                                information was received this morning and I hasten to communicate
                                it</p>
                            <p>I have the honor, &amp;c., &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>JOHN A. DIX.</signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>His Excellency the <hi rend="smallcaps">Marquis de Moustier</hi>,
                                        <hi rend="italic">Minister of Foreign Affairs.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>